From 687bf835b63214e7aa1b3a2710bd362d2d16bb4d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Abhilash G <abhilashg@nvidia.com>
Date: Thu, 16 Feb 2023 12:27:15 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 9/9] UBUNTU: SAUCE: scsi: ufs: Export query functions

BugLink: https://bugs.launchpad.net/bugs/2012939

Export ufshcd_query_attr and ufshcd_query_descriptor_retry
functions which are used for UFS provisioning and changing
reference clock frequency using sysfs nodes.

Also, Add config flag to find out that UFS query APIs are exported
or not from the given kernel.

Upstream-Status: Pending
Signed-off-by: Abhilash G <abhilashg@nvidia.com>
Reviewed-by: Laxman Dewangan <ldewangan@nvidia.com>
Reviewed-by: Bitan Biswas <bbiswas@nvidia.com>
Signed-off-by: Kartik <kkartik@nvidia.com>
Tested-by: Laxman Dewangan <ldewangan@nvidia.com>
Signed-off-by: Abhilash G <abhilashg@nvidia.com>
Acked-by: Brad Figg <bfigg@nvidia.com>
Acked-by: Ian May <ian.may@canonical.com>
Acked-by: Jacob Martin <jacob.martin@canonical.com>
Signed-off-by: Brad Figg <bfigg@nvidia.com>
---
 drivers/ufs/core/Kconfig  | 8 ++++++++
 drivers/ufs/core/ufshcd.c | 2 ++
 2 files changed, 10 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/ufs/core/Kconfig b/drivers/ufs/core/Kconfig
index 817208ee64ec..ec26b5b00b81 100644
--- a/drivers/ufs/core/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/ufs/core/Kconfig
@@ -50,3 +50,11 @@ config SCSI_UFS_HWMON
 	  a hardware monitoring device will be created for the UFS device.
 
 	  If unsure, say N.
+
+config SCSI_UFSHCD_QUERY_EXPORT
+	bool "UFS HCD QUERY APIS exported"
+	def_bool y
+	depends on SCSI_UFSHCD
+	help
+	  Export the  UFS HCD query APIs for provisioning the UFS. This config will
+	  tell whether APIs are exported or not.
diff --git a/drivers/ufs/core/ufshcd.c b/drivers/ufs/core/ufshcd.c
index 808979a09350..24d01ce0fdfb 100644
--- a/drivers/ufs/core/ufshcd.c
+++ b/drivers/ufs/core/ufshcd.c
@@ -3344,6 +3344,7 @@ int ufshcd_query_attr(struct ufs_hba *hba, enum query_opcode opcode,
 	ufshcd_release(hba);
 	return err;
 }
+EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(ufshcd_query_attr);
 
 /**
  * ufshcd_query_attr_retry() - API function for sending query
@@ -3477,6 +3478,7 @@ int ufshcd_query_descriptor_retry(struct ufs_hba *hba,
 
 	return err;
 }
+EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(ufshcd_query_descriptor_retry);
 
 /**
  * ufshcd_read_desc_param - read the specified descriptor parameter
-- 
